# Mock project credentials — TEMPLATE form.
#
# The literal Stripe / OpenAI / GitHub prefixes trigger GitHub's
# push-protection secret scanner even when followed by obvious
# filler text — repo can't ship with them committed.  So this
# template uses inert placeholders that ``setup.sh`` substitutes
# into real-shaped values at demo HOME stage time.  The ``.env``
# file produced at runtime contains DEMOFAKE-suffixed values that
# fire Sponsio's capability/credentials regex but are never valid
# against any real provider.
#
# Substitutions performed by setup.sh:
#   __STRIPE_KEY__   → real-shaped Stripe live key (DEMOFAKE-suffixed)
#   __OPENAI_KEY__   → real-shaped OpenAI project key (DEMOFAKE-suffixed)
#   __GITHUB_PAT__   → real-shaped GitHub PAT (DEMOFAKE-suffixed)
#   __SLACK_BOT__    → real-shaped Slack bot token (DEMOFAKE-suffixed)
#   __GOOGLE_API__   → real-shaped Google API key (DEMOFAKE-suffixed)
#
# Anyone reviewing this file directly: the placeholders are
# intentional, not a bug — see setup.sh for the mapping.

STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=__STRIPE_KEY__
OPENAI_API_KEY=__OPENAI_KEY__
GITHUB_TOKEN=__GITHUB_PAT__
SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=__SLACK_BOT__
GOOGLE_API_KEY=__GOOGLE_API__
DATABASE_URL=postgres://app:app@localhost:5432/myapp
SENTRY_DSN=https://demo-fake@o123456.ingest.sentry.io/1234567
LOG_LEVEL=info
PORT=3000
